WEBVTT

00:06.500 --> 00:08.125
[Bailey] <i>My mom used to tell me</i>

00:08.208 --> 00:10.667
<i>never to judge people</i>
<i>until you know their story.</i>

00:10.750 --> 00:11.875
Yeah. I can do that.

00:11.959 --> 00:14.625
<i>♪ Just talk to me now ♪</i>

00:14.792 --> 00:19.083
<i>♪ I'll help with those demons you carry ♪</i>

00:19.166 --> 00:21.750
<i>You might think you understand,</i>

00:21.834 --> 00:23.041
<i>but you don't.</i>

00:23.125 --> 00:25.458
<i>♪ I don't know if they go ♪</i>

00:25.542 --> 00:28.166
<i>That's why, as a patient,</i>

00:28.250 --> 00:30.500
<i>it's important </i><i>to have an advocate.</i>

00:30.583 --> 00:33.458
<i>♪ But we'll be happy someday, too ♪</i>

00:33.542 --> 00:35.750
[cellphone rings]

00:35.834 --> 00:37.083
Perfect timing.

00:37.291 --> 00:39.291
I just finished my last
tele-health patient.

00:39.375 --> 00:41.000
<i>Oh, I just woke up.</i>

00:41.083 --> 00:42.959
Aw. How'd you sleep?

00:43.041 --> 00:44.792
Would have slept better
if you were laying next to me.

00:44.875 --> 00:47.375
[Bailey] <i>Someone to tell your story,</i>
<i>to be your voice...</i>

00:47.458 --> 00:49.291
[speaks indistinctly]

00:49.375 --> 00:50.792
<i>...to say your name.</i>

00:51.709 --> 00:55.166
<i>Especially when you don't</i>
<i>have the voice yourself.</i>

00:55.250 --> 00:57.333
<i>♪ The great divide ♪</i>

00:57.417 --> 01:00.041
Her oxygen requirements
have come down this much?

01:00.125 --> 01:02.041
Ah. Cytokine storm's leveling off, too.

01:02.125 --> 01:04.458
I mean, look at her CRP, ferritin.

01:05.000 --> 01:06.333
That is great.

01:06.417 --> 01:07.917
Oh, I ordered a repeat chest X-ray

01:07.959 --> 01:09.625
to see if the infiltrates
are decreasing, too.

01:09.709 --> 01:11.500
You talk to her? She feel any better?

01:11.583 --> 01:13.166
Just long enough to tell her
that we got her into

01:13.250 --> 01:15.500
the drug trial.
But she's pretty exhausted.

01:15.583 --> 01:17.208
Well, it's probably the side effects.

01:17.291 --> 01:19.875
And she can sleep all day
if these numbers keep improving.

01:19.959 --> 01:21.291
Keep me posted.

01:21.375 --> 01:23.208
<i>♪ That you are not alone ♪</i>

01:23.291 --> 01:25.375
Jo? Good morning.

01:25.458 --> 01:27.417
It's time to get up.

01:27.500 --> 01:28.959
<i>♪ Afloat ♪</i>

01:29.041 --> 01:31.333
<i>♪ It's a brand-new day ♪</i>

01:31.417 --> 01:32.709
<i>♪ The sun is out to play ♪</i>

01:32.792 --> 01:34.667
God, will you shut up? I'm awake.

01:34.750 --> 01:36.917
Oh, okay. Are you going to work?

01:37.000 --> 01:38.041
Yes.

01:38.709 --> 01:40.750
At the regular time or...?

01:40.834 --> 01:42.917
[sighs]

01:43.000 --> 01:44.208
Everything okay?

01:44.959 --> 01:47.083
Oh, yeah, everything's great.

01:47.667 --> 01:49.709
I barely get to operate anymore,

01:49.792 --> 01:52.583
and when I do, they don't even
recover enough to go home.

01:52.667 --> 01:54.041
Oh, and how could I forget

01:54.125 --> 01:57.792
the refrigerator truck full of dead bodies

01:57.875 --> 01:59.959
that I get to pass on the way
from the parking lot

02:00.041 --> 02:01.500
to the hospital?

02:02.125 --> 02:03.875
The only reason I'm still in bed

02:03.959 --> 02:06.625
is that I am paralyzed with excitement.

02:09.083 --> 02:11.041
-So you're going?
-Why do you care?

02:11.125 --> 02:13.208
My bike has a flat tire,
and you're my ride.

02:14.291 --> 02:15.625
[sighs]

02:15.709 --> 02:18.750
[William] <i>She said</i>
<i>the salad I made was too small.</i>

02:18.834 --> 02:21.000
<i>So I go back and make her a bigger one.</i>

02:21.083 --> 02:23.125
<i>She says I must hate her</i>
<i>because it's too big.</i>

02:23.208 --> 02:24.417
-[Bailey] Mm.
<i>-I just can't win.</i>

02:24.500 --> 02:26.291
No, she appreciates you, Dad.

02:26.375 --> 02:28.458
It's not her. It's the dementia.

02:28.542 --> 02:30.959
[William] <i>Knowing that</i>
<i>doesn't make it hurt any less.</i>

02:31.083 --> 02:32.250
We're gonna get through this.

02:32.333 --> 02:34.709
<i>We? I only see you on the phone.</i>

02:34.792 --> 02:37.250
<i>And you can't even bother</i>
<i>to hold the thing still.</i>

02:37.333 --> 02:38.917
I have a hospital to run.

02:39.000 --> 02:40.667
And I didn't know there'd be a pandemic.

02:40.750 --> 02:42.291
<i>Ben's sister gets to stay with you.</i>

02:42.375 --> 02:43.917
To-- With the boys.

02:44.291 --> 02:46.000
Who I don't see either.

02:46.083 --> 02:48.250
Ben's staying at the station,

02:48.333 --> 02:51.667
and half the time, I'm too tired
to make it to my hotel.

02:51.750 --> 02:55.291
I promise Silver Villas is
more comfortable than my office.

02:55.583 --> 02:58.625
<i>I just hate this. I hate all of it.</i>

02:58.709 --> 03:00.041
<i>It's not fair.</i>

03:00.125 --> 03:01.834
Well, COVID's not big on fair.

03:01.917 --> 03:03.291
Listen, I have to go.

03:03.375 --> 03:04.667
I love you.

03:06.417 --> 03:08.500
Don't go outside, Dad, okay?
It's not safe.

03:08.583 --> 03:11.375
[William] <i>Tell your mom that. She's</i>
<i>the one always trying to leave.</i>

03:11.458 --> 03:13.417
-[sighs]
-[smooches] I love you, too.

03:13.500 --> 03:14.625
[smooches]

03:15.458 --> 03:17.333
[Woman over P.A.]
<i>Dr. Wakeman to Neurology.</i>

03:17.417 --> 03:19.083
<i>Dr. Wakeman to Neurology.</i>

03:19.166 --> 03:20.291
[sighs]

03:21.417 --> 03:22.709
[Richard] Ah. Good morning, Avery.

03:22.792 --> 03:24.000
[Jackson] Not really.

03:24.083 --> 03:25.667
You know how many trachs
I've had to do this week

03:25.750 --> 03:27.625
on long-term vent patients
'cause of COVID?

03:27.709 --> 03:29.542
No, but I have a feeling
you're gonna tell me.

03:29.625 --> 03:31.000
11, Richard.

03:31.083 --> 03:32.583
Gonna be 12 in about an hour,

03:32.667 --> 03:34.208
and this number's gonna keep on going up,

03:34.291 --> 03:36.375
which is why I need you
to help me with this.

03:36.458 --> 03:39.000
[Richard] Oh, when did your mother
go to San Francisco?

03:39.083 --> 03:41.041
What? No, no. That's a--
That's a fake video background

03:41.125 --> 03:42.875
for when she talks to Harriet.
That's not the point. Look.

03:42.959 --> 03:44.291
You want her to change the background?

03:44.375 --> 03:46.709
I want you to get your wife
to wear a damn mask, okay?

03:46.792 --> 03:49.709
She's in a germ-collecting car
with her driver with no mask.

03:49.792 --> 03:50.959
She wears masks.

03:51.041 --> 03:52.667
On her chin, okay,

03:52.750 --> 03:55.166
or dangling from her ear
like a weird piece of jewelry.

03:55.250 --> 03:58.166
She is living with cancer.
She is immunocompromised.

03:58.542 --> 03:59.542
I got to get to surgery.

03:59.625 --> 04:01.375
Just get her to wear the stupid
mask correctly, please.

04:02.000 --> 04:03.041
Well, you know what it's like

04:03.125 --> 04:04.375
to get your mother to do something!

04:04.542 --> 04:07.166
Yeah, that's why
I'm calling for reinforcements.

04:10.417 --> 04:12.792
[Reza] Val Ashton,
status post right hepatectomy

04:12.875 --> 04:14.250
with segments 5 through 8

04:14.333 --> 04:16.417
due to bleeding from hepatic pregnancy.

04:16.500 --> 04:17.583
Her drains were pulled two days ago,

04:17.667 --> 04:19.291
but this morning she's tachy to 120,

04:19.375 --> 04:20.583
her BP has decreased,

04:20.667 --> 04:23.000
and transaminases and bili
are both trending upwards.

04:23.083 --> 04:24.959
[Val] She's kind, giving, successful,

04:25.041 --> 04:27.125
enjoys a raunchy romance novel.

04:27.208 --> 04:29.041
Without shame. [chuckles]

04:29.125 --> 04:31.000
I need compliments, too, guys.

04:31.083 --> 04:33.083
[Jo] I'm glad that you're
in good spirits, Val,

04:33.166 --> 04:36.667
but, um, your labs are concerning.

04:36.750 --> 04:37.959
I'm ordering a CT.

04:38.041 --> 04:40.583
I carried a baby in my liver.

04:40.667 --> 04:43.959
Can't you make an exception for
moms and babies who defy odds?

04:45.083 --> 04:47.041
I-I'm sick of video chats.

04:47.125 --> 04:50.125
Luna's gonna think
her mom's a pixelated blob.

04:50.208 --> 04:52.792
[Levi] Technically, that's what
you'd look like even in person.

04:52.875 --> 04:54.417
Babies can only see
about six inches in front--

04:54.500 --> 04:56.333
[Jo] Schmitt! Not the point.

04:57.291 --> 04:59.417
Val, I know that it's not
what you wanted to hear,

04:59.500 --> 05:03.041
but Luna's on a vent, and
moving her is very precarious.

05:03.125 --> 05:05.125
Plus, we-- we need to make sure
that you're taken care of

05:05.208 --> 05:06.417
before you meet her.

05:06.500 --> 05:08.750
For Luna's sake and for yours.

05:08.834 --> 05:10.291
Okay?

05:12.041 --> 05:14.250
[siren wailing]

05:14.333 --> 05:15.625
Do we know if he's okay?

05:15.709 --> 05:17.834
Not sure. This is him.

05:17.917 --> 05:19.083
[Koracick] You're not listening--

05:19.166 --> 05:20.917
I have to be at home.
I don't want to miss it--

05:21.000 --> 05:22.000
Oh, my God.

05:22.083 --> 05:23.625
[Paramedic] Okay,
we have a COVID-positive male,

05:23.709 --> 05:25.500
heart rate 123, BP 90 over 60.

05:25.583 --> 05:28.166
Pulse Ox of 92 on 100%, high flow.

05:28.250 --> 05:29.917
He's incoherent and disoriented.

05:30.000 --> 05:32.000
[Taryn] I just saw him
two days ago. He was fine.

05:32.083 --> 05:33.458
Is this a stroke?

05:33.542 --> 05:35.166
Could be. Or encephalitis
brought on by COVID.

05:35.250 --> 05:36.583
[Koracick] I have tickets to Opening Day,

05:36.667 --> 05:38.000
and David's dying to catch a fly ball.

05:38.083 --> 05:39.458
-[Taryn] Who's David?
-His son.

05:39.542 --> 05:41.458
Let's get him to a COVID room now.

05:41.542 --> 05:43.000
Hang on. He's seizing.

05:44.417 --> 05:45.750
Let's get him on his side.

05:45.834 --> 05:47.333
-Ready? One, two, three.
-[Koracick gasping]

05:57.875 --> 06:00.041
[Teddy] No signs of head trauma,
but, Helm, call up to CT,

06:00.125 --> 06:01.667
let them know we'll be up
as soon as possible.

06:01.750 --> 06:03.417
[Owen] We'll do it. Helm, out.

06:03.500 --> 06:04.959
[Taryn] But I've already had COVID --

06:05.041 --> 06:06.417
Doesn't matter. You're a resident,

06:06.500 --> 06:07.750
and he's positive. Out. Now.

06:08.417 --> 06:10.125
Get off me. Stay back.

06:10.208 --> 06:12.375
Tom. Tom, it's me.
It's Teddy. Try to stay calm.

06:12.458 --> 06:14.291
-[Koracick] I-- Don't-- Don't touch me.
-[Teddy] Tom?

06:14.375 --> 06:15.667
Take it easy. We're just trying
to take care of you.

06:15.750 --> 06:17.458
-Push two of Ativan.
-No, I don't-- I don't know you.

06:17.542 --> 06:18.583
-I don't know you!
-He's postictal.

06:18.667 --> 06:19.834
Just wait a minute,
and the meds will kick in.

06:19.917 --> 06:21.166
No, I don't-- I don't know you.

06:21.667 --> 06:23.417
[grunting softly]

06:23.500 --> 06:24.959
-[sighs]
-Teddy, I got this, okay?

06:25.709 --> 06:27.208
Please, call up to CT.

06:30.959 --> 06:32.000
Okay.

06:33.542 --> 06:35.542
[Val[ Hey, Angel.

06:35.625 --> 06:39.083
I'd be there with you,
but the mean doctors say no.

06:39.166 --> 06:40.917
Can you say "mean"?

06:41.417 --> 06:44.959
Can you hold the phone close
enough for me to smell her head?

06:45.041 --> 06:46.959
[Reza] How about I bring you
one of her blankets?

06:47.041 --> 06:49.834
Ah! I will literally marry you.

06:49.917 --> 06:51.500
[Jo] Val.

06:51.583 --> 06:54.667
Crap. That is your bad-news face.

06:54.750 --> 06:57.583
Your CT showed that you have an abscess

06:57.667 --> 07:00.250
that's eroding into an artery
in your liver,

07:00.333 --> 07:02.792
causing what's called a pseudoaneurysm.

07:02.875 --> 07:04.000
Okay.

07:04.083 --> 07:05.458
[Levi] It's a weakening
of the blood vessel,

07:05.542 --> 07:06.834
which is causing it to leak.

07:06.917 --> 07:08.792
We need to take you to surgery
right away to repair it.

07:08.875 --> 07:11.542
I am so sorry that it's not better news.

07:12.500 --> 07:13.834
[cellphone clatters]

07:15.375 --> 07:16.458
Leave.

07:17.250 --> 07:19.041
[monitor beeping]

07:19.458 --> 07:20.917
[door closes]

07:21.709 --> 07:22.959
[Val] Eight years.

07:24.625 --> 07:28.083
I've wanted to be a mom for eight years.

07:29.000 --> 07:31.208
I've known my baby's name.

07:32.250 --> 07:34.834
I've known the color
I would paint the nursery.

07:34.917 --> 07:38.000
I've known the made-up lullaby
I would sing at night.

07:38.875 --> 07:41.125
And now that I finally have the chance...

07:41.917 --> 07:44.041
being a mom is just some weird TV show

07:44.125 --> 07:46.125
I'm watching on my phone,

07:46.208 --> 07:49.125
and I don't know if it will ever be real.

07:50.083 --> 07:51.583
[crying]

07:51.667 --> 07:55.041
Please make it real.

07:57.625 --> 07:59.208
[Maggie] Have you heard about Koracick?

07:59.291 --> 08:01.583
[Bailey] Yes. He's getting
the world's best care,

08:01.667 --> 08:03.333
and I'm trying not to think about it.

08:03.417 --> 08:06.709
So, can you wait that long
for the converted rooms?

08:06.792 --> 08:08.417
Is sooner an option?

08:08.500 --> 08:10.250
See, even with the lockdown,
we are getting slammed.

08:10.333 --> 08:12.875
We got six cases today from
assisted-living facilities,

08:12.959 --> 08:14.583
-three from the same one.
-[Woman] I'll go check.

08:14.667 --> 08:17.500
-Oh, which one?
-Silver Villas in Ballard.

08:17.583 --> 08:20.000
COVID spreads through
those places like wildfire.

08:20.083 --> 08:21.125
Where are you going?

08:21.208 --> 08:23.625
Uh, that's where my parents are.

08:23.709 --> 08:25.458
-A rescue mission?
-[Bailey] <i>Yes.</i>

08:25.542 --> 08:27.834
Just stop what you're doing
and get to Silver Villas.

08:27.917 --> 08:29.041
To grab your mom and dad?

08:29.125 --> 08:30.458
I've been trying to call the front office,

08:30.542 --> 08:31.667
but they're not answering.

08:31.750 --> 08:32.750
Where do you want me to take them?

08:32.834 --> 08:34.375
Uh, to my hotel.

08:34.458 --> 08:36.208
Y-- Uh, I don't care. Just get them out.

08:36.291 --> 08:38.041
Yeah, I'm on it. I love you.

08:39.291 --> 08:40.458
[click, siren wailing]

08:44.917 --> 08:46.375
-[Jo] Okay, lap pads.
-[Reza] Here you go.

08:47.625 --> 08:49.333
[Levi] Khan was an attending in Pakistan.

08:50.125 --> 08:51.458
We could probably be assisting <i>him.</i>

08:51.542 --> 08:52.917
Not gonna happen.

08:53.000 --> 08:55.083
No, I know. I just-- making a point.

08:55.166 --> 08:56.125
Suction.

08:56.208 --> 08:57.625
You were a vascular surgeon, right?

08:57.709 --> 09:00.083
[Reza] Yes, Dr. Schmitt, one of the first
to be certified in my country.

09:00.542 --> 09:02.041
Why would you leave?

09:02.125 --> 09:03.208
Okay, Kelly clamp.

09:03.291 --> 09:05.000
Uh, it wasn't exactly a choice.

09:05.083 --> 09:07.083
I love my home, it shaped me.

09:07.166 --> 09:09.000
Still nice not to worry
about religious persecution

09:09.083 --> 09:10.667
-or bombings, so...
-[Jo] Clamp.

09:10.750 --> 09:12.041
I just started over.

09:12.125 --> 09:14.583
Just? It's a five-year residency.

09:14.667 --> 09:16.333
If I finished this
and had to start over--

09:16.417 --> 09:18.583
Ugh. Pass. Can you imagine?

09:18.667 --> 09:20.500
Can you imagine paying
more attention to the field

09:20.583 --> 09:22.083
so the patient doesn't die?

09:22.166 --> 09:24.000
Damn it. Her tissue's so friable

09:24.083 --> 09:25.875
it's just disintegrating into my hands.

09:25.959 --> 09:27.625
-We got to get control of--
-I know what we need to do!

09:27.709 --> 09:30.083
Everyone shift. We're doing
a modified pringle maneuver.

09:30.166 --> 09:31.375
Clamp.

09:36.333 --> 09:37.750
[Maggie] Okay, thank you.

09:37.834 --> 09:40.166
Hey. Your phone has been ringing
like crazy.

09:40.250 --> 09:41.583
Oh?

09:44.166 --> 09:46.875
-Oh, wow. Okay.
-[cellphone chiming]

09:46.959 --> 09:48.542
Uh, okay. Let's just, uh...

09:48.625 --> 09:50.834
-Ben! How did it --
-[Ben] I tried to call you.

09:50.917 --> 09:52.333
I picked up your mom,
and she's sick.

09:52.417 --> 09:53.542
Wait, slow down. I ca--

09:53.625 --> 09:54.834
-We're at the hospital.
-Now?

09:54.917 --> 09:56.375
[Ben] Right now.

09:58.125 --> 09:59.166
Mom!

10:00.458 --> 10:02.625
[labored breathing]

10:04.917 --> 10:07.125
Mom? Hey, it's me.

10:07.792 --> 10:09.000
I'm here.

10:14.291 --> 10:16.583
-William?
-[Maggie] All right, okay.

10:16.667 --> 10:18.000
[gasping] Where--
Where-- Where's William?

10:18.083 --> 10:19.834
Mom, you're in the hospital.

10:19.917 --> 10:21.250
We're gonna take care of you.

10:21.333 --> 10:22.625
He's gonna be here soon, right?

10:22.709 --> 10:25.166
-Okay.
-Yes, yes. He's coming soon.

10:25.250 --> 10:27.083
Just lay back and relax.

10:27.458 --> 10:30.041
I can't wear this.
I got to get my clothes.

10:30.125 --> 10:31.208
Where my clothes?

10:31.291 --> 10:33.041
Okay. She seems really agitated.

10:33.125 --> 10:34.917
Are there any meds
we can give her to calm her?

10:35.000 --> 10:36.709
-I can order some meds?
-[grunts]

10:38.208 --> 10:41.667
<i>♪ I got sunshine ♪</i>

10:43.041 --> 10:45.875
<i>♪ On a cloudy day ♪</i>

10:47.250 --> 10:51.500
<i>-♪ When it's cold outside ♪</i>
<i>-♪ Cold outside ♪</i>

10:52.667 --> 10:55.375
<i>-♪ I got the month of May ♪</i>
<i>-♪ I got the month of May ♪</i>

10:57.750 --> 11:03.000
<i>-♪ I guess you'd say ♪</i>
<i>-♪ I guess you'd say ♪</i>

11:03.959 --> 11:09.792
<i>-♪ What can make me feel this way? ♪</i>
<i>-♪ What can make me feel... way? ♪</i>

11:09.959 --> 11:13.166
<i>-♪ My girl ♪</i>
<i>-♪ My girl ♪</i>

11:13.250 --> 11:14.625
<i>♪ My girl ♪</i>

11:14.709 --> 11:17.250
[chuckles] <i>♪ Talking 'bout ♪</i>

11:17.333 --> 11:19.959
<i>♪ My girl ♪</i>

11:21.250 --> 11:23.667
<i>♪ My girl ♪</i>

11:23.750 --> 11:25.667
[monitor beeping]

11:27.500 --> 11:28.792
What do you see, Shepherd?

11:28.875 --> 11:30.667
Uh, I see a lesion on his thalamus,

11:30.750 --> 11:32.709
but it's small, so that's something.

11:32.792 --> 11:34.917
Have you been able to talk
to him since the seizure?

11:35.000 --> 11:36.834
He was postictal,
and they gave him lorazepam,

11:36.917 --> 11:38.500
so he wasn't really coherent.

11:38.583 --> 11:41.333
Okay. I'm coming in.

11:41.417 --> 11:43.750
[Teddy] <i>Are-- Are you sure? I mean, do</i>
<i>you want me to call Dr. Mehta?</i>

11:43.834 --> 11:45.250
It's Tom. I'm coming.

11:45.333 --> 11:46.500
Thank you.

11:47.667 --> 11:50.709
[Link] Uh, Ellis decided she didn't
want her mac and cheese

11:50.792 --> 11:53.208
after begging me to make it,
so if you're hungry--

11:54.709 --> 11:56.458
-What's going on?
-[sighs]

11:56.542 --> 11:59.208
It looks like Tom is having some
neuro-complications from COVID.

11:59.291 --> 12:01.542
-I thought he was asymptomatic.
-Yeah, so did I.

12:01.959 --> 12:04.417
I just pumped, so there is milk
in the fridge for Scout.

12:04.500 --> 12:06.083
Uh, Bailey and Ellis need a nap.

12:06.166 --> 12:08.291
Make sure you check in with Zola
about her homework.

12:08.709 --> 12:11.917
If Scout starts to fuss,
just try the yoga ball.

12:12.041 --> 12:13.750
What am I forgetting?

12:13.834 --> 12:15.375
-To breathe.
-[sighs]

12:15.458 --> 12:18.750
We'll be fine here, okay?
Go. Save your friend.

12:18.834 --> 12:20.500
-[baby fussing]
-[sighs]

12:20.583 --> 12:23.417
He was my teacher. And he saved my brain.

12:23.500 --> 12:26.041
And, uh, he was my first sex after Owen,

12:26.125 --> 12:27.834
which shouldn't matter,
but it kind of saved me, too,

12:27.917 --> 12:30.417
so I don't want him to die.

12:30.500 --> 12:34.667
And I don't want to leave Scout,
and I'm scared of the pandemic.

12:34.750 --> 12:36.458
You had sex with Koracick?

12:36.542 --> 12:37.625
What?

12:41.583 --> 12:44.417
[door opens, closes]

12:45.291 --> 12:48.041
[Jackson] Hey. Oh, um,
Mr. Anderson's trach in 4722

12:48.125 --> 12:49.792
-needs to be suctioned, please.
-I'm on it.

12:49.875 --> 12:51.709
Hey, got your page.
Did you hear anything from Mom?

12:51.792 --> 12:53.709
She's just texting me back
hearts and "Love you, baby"s

12:53.792 --> 12:55.125
like that's gonna shut me up.

12:55.208 --> 12:57.333
-No, I haven't had the time.
-Richard, this is not something

12:57.417 --> 12:59.208
that can wait till your schedule
frees up, right?

12:59.291 --> 13:00.875
It's my mom. She's gonna give me
a damn rage stroke.

13:00.959 --> 13:04.458
Bailey's mother was just admitted,
COVID-positive.

13:04.542 --> 13:05.750
It's bad.

13:05.834 --> 13:08.166
Look, can you fill in for her
at the board meeting today,

13:08.250 --> 13:10.250
take a few of her patients?

13:10.333 --> 13:11.458
We'll all pitch in.

13:12.166 --> 13:14.166
Yeah, of course. Whatever she needs.

13:17.667 --> 13:20.875
[Jo] We took a lot more of
her liver than I was hoping to.

13:20.959 --> 13:22.250
Keep an eye on her liver panel.

13:22.333 --> 13:24.000
The next few hours will be crucial.

13:24.083 --> 13:25.083
[Levi] You think she'll need a transplant?

13:25.166 --> 13:26.959
Knowing her luck, probably.

13:27.542 --> 13:30.709
But if she needs it,
we can try liver dialysis first.

13:30.792 --> 13:33.834
Khan, finish the op notes.
Keep an eye on her.

13:33.917 --> 13:36.750
Dr. Wilson, thank you
for allowing me to observe your process.

13:36.834 --> 13:38.458
That was amazing.

13:38.542 --> 13:40.375
She could still need a transplant.

13:40.458 --> 13:42.709
Yes, I understand, but
you resected most of her liver,

13:42.792 --> 13:44.083
and she's still alive.

13:44.166 --> 13:45.917
I mean, do you know how rare that is?

13:46.000 --> 13:48.667
That-- That's unheard of
in so many parts of the world.

13:48.750 --> 13:51.250
I know. Op notes. I'm going.

13:52.875 --> 13:54.917
[sighs] Was I really amazing,

13:55.000 --> 13:57.583
or is he just some weird happy person?

13:57.667 --> 14:00.959
If you impressed <i>him,</i>
I think amazing's a safe bet.

14:03.375 --> 14:04.917
Glad you got to operate again.

14:06.417 --> 14:07.375
[door opens]

14:07.458 --> 14:09.166
[sighs]

14:10.709 --> 14:13.000
[Bailey] Her ferritin is 2087.

14:13.083 --> 14:15.208
600 is severe in COVID.

14:15.291 --> 14:18.500
Her CRP is 87.

14:18.583 --> 14:21.125
Creatinine's 2.3.

14:21.208 --> 14:23.291
W-What about her oxygen requirements?

14:23.375 --> 14:24.709
<i>♪ Caught swimming in your new sundress ♪</i>

14:24.792 --> 14:27.083
[sighs] She's at 100% FiO2.

14:27.166 --> 14:28.250
40 liters.

14:29.375 --> 14:31.500
She went into A-fib an hour ago.

14:31.583 --> 14:34.208
We pushed dig, but so far, no response.

14:36.041 --> 14:38.792
Her systolic was in the 80s,
but we pushed a fluid bolus

14:38.875 --> 14:40.458
and got it back up into the 90s.

14:41.166 --> 14:45.917
So she's starting to have
multi-system organ failure

14:46.000 --> 14:47.875
in addition to her cytokine storm.

14:48.458 --> 14:50.000
I'm sorry, Bailey.

14:52.834 --> 14:54.250
There is still more we can do.

14:54.333 --> 14:57.041
We can take her to the ICU, intubate--

14:57.125 --> 14:59.458
She didn't want to be on machines.

14:59.542 --> 15:02.667
Or be kept alive with medication.

15:08.583 --> 15:10.875
I got to call my dad. Um...

15:13.417 --> 15:15.041
I'm here if you need me.

15:17.250 --> 15:19.333
H-How-- How do I tell my dad

15:19.417 --> 15:22.834
that... the love of his life...

15:23.875 --> 15:25.917
won't make it through the night?

15:37.125 --> 15:38.458
[telephone rings in distance]

15:41.834 --> 15:44.250
[Amelia] Neuro exam's intact. No deficits.

15:44.333 --> 15:45.792
He asked for his son.

15:45.875 --> 15:49.959
I think the seizure and delirium
are secondary to hypoxemia

15:50.041 --> 15:53.291
and inflammation from COVID--
possible early sepsis.

15:53.375 --> 15:56.125
Let's just watch him and, uh...
see how he responds to treatment.

15:56.208 --> 15:57.083
Okay.

15:57.208 --> 15:58.792
Oh, hey, Shepherd.
Didn't realize you were back.

15:58.875 --> 16:00.375
Welcome to... hell.

16:00.458 --> 16:02.250
Just consulting on Koracick.

16:02.333 --> 16:04.166
Oh, right, 'cause he needs
somebody to cover his service.

16:04.250 --> 16:06.250
<i>On </i>him, not-- uh, not <i>for </i>him.

16:06.333 --> 16:08.417
Sats dropped, he's got a fever of 103,

16:08.500 --> 16:10.125
and he seized when they brought him in.

16:10.208 --> 16:13.250
[sighs] Well, I hate everything.

16:13.333 --> 16:16.291
[Woman over P.A.] <i>Dr. Cade to</i>
<i>the ICU. Emma Cade to the ICU.</i>

16:16.375 --> 16:17.834
I was wondering if you get used to this,

16:17.917 --> 16:19.583
but I'm guessing that's my answer.

16:20.083 --> 16:21.166
How's the baby?

16:21.500 --> 16:23.667
Uh, yeah, uh, well, he won't let me sleep,

16:23.750 --> 16:26.834
but other than that, um, yeah,
I can't wait to get back to him.

16:26.917 --> 16:28.750
Leo and Allison are with Owen's mom.

16:28.834 --> 16:30.417
I'm just-- I miss them like crazy,

16:30.500 --> 16:32.750
but with both parents
treating COVID patients,

16:32.834 --> 16:34.667
it just-- it doesn't seem safe.

16:34.750 --> 16:35.792
Uh-huh.

16:36.583 --> 16:39.458
So, um, guess you heard what happened.

16:39.542 --> 16:42.125
Yeah. And I have feelings.

16:42.667 --> 16:44.417
But I've also done

16:44.500 --> 16:46.917
more hurtful and complicated
things in my life

16:47.000 --> 16:49.667
than anyone I've met
outside an NA meeting, so--

16:49.750 --> 16:50.875
some of them to Owen.

16:51.625 --> 16:53.083
Owen won't say a word to me

16:53.166 --> 16:54.250
that doesn't have to do with the kids,

16:54.333 --> 16:56.875
and everyone is ignoring me

16:56.959 --> 16:59.959
or treating me like
I'm wearing a scarlet letter.

17:00.041 --> 17:01.291
What about Tom?

17:02.250 --> 17:03.667
He's hurt, too.

17:05.000 --> 17:07.709
Well, um, I'll keep checking on him.

17:07.792 --> 17:11.500
And, uh, thank you
for getting Mer into the trial.

17:11.583 --> 17:13.709
Oh, yeah, uh, of course. [sighs]

17:15.625 --> 17:17.625
[monitor beeping]

17:18.250 --> 17:20.208
Hi, Grey.

17:20.750 --> 17:21.834
It's me.

17:22.750 --> 17:24.500
I'm gonna say it.

17:25.000 --> 17:26.125
I miss you.

17:32.000 --> 17:33.083
[sighs]

17:35.959 --> 17:39.917
When I was a kid, I had big thoughts.

17:40.625 --> 17:42.166
Big feelings.

17:42.250 --> 17:44.208
And I never knew where to put them.

17:45.375 --> 17:49.792
Physically, they ran through
my body like a high-speed train.

17:50.458 --> 17:53.041
And anytime I felt the train coming,

17:53.291 --> 17:55.834
my mom could see it.

17:56.542 --> 17:59.417
So she took me around the corner
to the park

17:59.500 --> 18:03.583
with this strange, twisted tree.

18:04.500 --> 18:06.417
Said it was <i>my </i>tree.

18:06.625 --> 18:10.333
And I could scream at it,
hit it, hold it--

18:10.417 --> 18:12.208
and it would make
the feelings small enough

18:12.291 --> 18:16.333
that they would fit back
inside of my own body again.

18:16.542 --> 18:18.500
So I did.

18:20.166 --> 18:21.625
And it worked.

18:22.250 --> 18:26.166
But now I'm an adult,
and tree-hitting is...

18:27.792 --> 18:29.333
[chuckling] frowned upon.

18:29.417 --> 18:31.208
I can be your tree.

18:33.000 --> 18:35.000
My mother has Alzheimer's.

18:37.250 --> 18:39.041
I never told you

18:39.125 --> 18:42.542
because she's older...

18:43.583 --> 18:46.417
and I didn't want to bring up any old pain

18:46.500 --> 18:49.125
for you or Richard.

18:49.250 --> 18:51.875
But it would be a lie

18:51.959 --> 18:55.291
to say that it hasn't been hard.

18:55.834 --> 18:57.208
Or painful.

18:58.417 --> 19:02.208
Even as a doctor
who knows about the disease,

19:03.166 --> 19:05.333
I feel like...

19:06.709 --> 19:07.709
I didn't know crap.

19:07.792 --> 19:09.667
...like I don't know anything.

19:12.041 --> 19:13.667
It's difficult to talk about it

19:13.750 --> 19:15.750
with someone who hasn't been there,

19:15.834 --> 19:17.333
been through it.

19:21.375 --> 19:24.041
No one understands that you are

19:24.125 --> 19:27.458
watching your own mother die...

19:27.542 --> 19:28.917
twice.

19:30.417 --> 19:32.250
I'm so sorry, Bailey.

19:34.000 --> 19:36.083
[crying] I wish you were awake.

19:46.125 --> 19:48.000
[Reza] Val's still not awake.
LFTs are up slightly.

19:48.083 --> 19:49.875
[Jo] Okay. Do another
panel in a few hours.

19:49.959 --> 19:51.834
Absolutely, Dr. Wilson.

19:51.917 --> 19:55.542
Okay, has your attitude
always been this good?

19:55.750 --> 19:58.542
My mom used to say every day
above ground is a good day.

19:59.083 --> 20:00.583
Did she get that from "Scarface"?

20:00.667 --> 20:03.709
-She did. Still, it's true.
-[elevator bell dings]

20:03.792 --> 20:05.375
-[sighs]
-[telephone rings]

20:05.458 --> 20:07.875
[Woman speaks indistinctly over P.A.]

20:07.959 --> 20:10.041
[Nurse Terri] You! You're a doctor, right?

20:10.125 --> 20:12.125
-Yeah.
-Great, follow me.

20:12.208 --> 20:13.750
-We're delivering a baby.
-Oh, no, no, no, no, no.

20:13.834 --> 20:15.500
-I'm not an OB, I'm a general surgeon.
-I don't care.

20:15.583 --> 20:17.375
We have an imminent delivery,
and all our OBs are busy.

20:17.458 --> 20:19.083
Hospital rules say we need a doctor.

20:19.166 --> 20:20.750
I haven't delivered a baby--

20:20.834 --> 20:22.208
You heard the "I don't care" part, right?

20:22.291 --> 20:23.333
We'll talk you through it.

20:23.417 --> 20:25.000
-The Elmores.
-Okay.

20:25.083 --> 20:28.000
G3P2 came in fully effaced
and dilated at zero station.

20:28.083 --> 20:30.542
Started crowning by the time
we got her settled on the bed.

20:30.625 --> 20:33.959
Ms. Elmore? Hi. I know
that I'm not who you expected,

20:34.083 --> 20:35.583
-but I am here--
-The head is coming now.

20:35.667 --> 20:37.458
-Hi.
-Hi.

20:37.542 --> 20:39.291
Okay. Okay.

20:39.375 --> 20:40.750
[Kathy panting]

20:40.834 --> 20:43.667
All right. Contraction and big push, okay?
Big push.

20:43.750 --> 20:45.917
[grunting]

20:46.000 --> 20:47.917
<i>♪ Told my troubled heart ♪</i>

20:48.000 --> 20:50.333
Okay. Contraction and push.

20:50.417 --> 20:52.041
[screaming]

20:52.125 --> 20:54.667
The head is out. There--
No cord around the neck.

20:54.750 --> 20:56.500
See? Just like riding a bike.

20:56.583 --> 20:58.083
All right, uh...

20:58.166 --> 21:00.792
[Nurse Terri] Pull head down, then up,
to deliver the shoulders.

21:00.875 --> 21:02.667
-Okay, it's coming.
-[screaming]

21:02.750 --> 21:04.333
It's coming.

21:04.417 --> 21:07.041
Oh, my God. [laughing] Oh, my God.

21:07.125 --> 21:09.625
Ms. Elmore asked that the baby
go directly onto her chest

21:09.709 --> 21:10.709
-while still connected.
-[baby crying]

21:10.792 --> 21:12.083
[Jo] Okay, clamp.

21:12.834 --> 21:15.959
Okay. Oh, my gosh. Okay.

21:16.083 --> 21:18.333
<i>♪ A new light shining down on me ♪</i>

21:18.417 --> 21:19.625
Okay.

21:19.709 --> 21:21.834
<i>♪ A new way, a new road ♪</i>

21:21.917 --> 21:23.875
[Jo] You ready to cut the cord?

21:24.834 --> 21:26.875
Hi. Okay, right here.

21:26.959 --> 21:28.542
Okay, yeah. In between here.

21:28.625 --> 21:29.917
In between, yeah.

21:30.542 --> 21:32.291
Good. Hi, little one!

21:32.375 --> 21:33.792
<i>♪ Take my hand ♪</i>

21:33.875 --> 21:35.208
-[laughs]
-[baby crying]

21:35.542 --> 21:40.959
<i>♪ The worst is over ♪</i>

21:41.583 --> 21:46.792
<i>♪ Weight is liftin' ♪</i>

21:46.875 --> 21:52.041
<i>♪ Off our shoulders ♪</i>

21:52.125 --> 21:54.709
<i>-♪ I can see ♪</i>
<i>-♪ Oh, I can see ♪</i>

21:54.792 --> 21:57.834
<i>-♪ I can see ♪</i>
<i>-♪ I can see ♪</i>

21:57.917 --> 22:00.458
<i>-♪ A new light ♪</i>
<i>-♪ New light ♪</i>

22:00.542 --> 22:03.750
<i>-♪ Shining down on me ♪</i>
<i>-♪ Down on me ♪</i>

22:03.834 --> 22:05.917
<i>♪ A new way, a new road ♪</i>

22:06.000 --> 22:07.834
Just need you to sign
the paperwork, and you can go.

22:08.208 --> 22:09.625
Is it all right if I stay?

22:10.875 --> 22:14.709
<i>♪ Oh, oh, to a new kind of beautiful ♪</i>

22:15.250 --> 22:18.000
Okay. Mommy?

22:18.083 --> 22:19.333
Hey, it's me.

22:19.583 --> 22:21.875
Look, Dad's here, too.

22:22.166 --> 22:24.667
<i>Hi, honey. I'm here.</i>

22:24.750 --> 22:27.041
<i>Wait till you see Miranda's hotel.</i>

22:27.125 --> 22:29.041
<i>I mean, there's room service,</i>

22:29.125 --> 22:31.792
<i>and the view is so much better</i>
<i>than Silver Villas.</i>

22:31.959 --> 22:34.500
<i>You can actually s-see the water.</i>

22:34.583 --> 22:36.458
[weakly] William?

22:36.542 --> 22:38.500
Is that you, William?

22:38.583 --> 22:41.000
<i>Right here by your side, as always.</i>

22:41.083 --> 22:44.166
<i>I love you. I love you so much.</i>

22:45.041 --> 22:47.125
<i>Sweetheart? </i>[crying]

22:47.208 --> 22:50.834
Uh, she drifts in and out, Dad.

22:51.375 --> 22:54.333
In her state, even breathing's exhausting.

22:54.792 --> 22:56.458
<i>I can't do this.</i>

22:56.959 --> 22:58.291
I know.

22:58.375 --> 23:00.000
It's difficult.

23:00.083 --> 23:01.417
<i>I should be there.</i>

23:01.500 --> 23:03.250
It's too risky, Dad.

23:03.333 --> 23:07.208
<i>She should be in her own bed,</i>
<i>not in some sterile box.</i>

23:07.291 --> 23:12.208
<i>She spent 60 years</i>
<i>taking care of me, and now...</i>

23:13.166 --> 23:15.875
<i>She hardly ever got a cold before this.</i>

23:16.917 --> 23:19.417
<i>Just call me when she wakes up.</i>

23:20.125 --> 23:22.000
[labored breathing]

23:22.083 --> 23:23.625
Of course, Dad.

23:32.291 --> 23:33.500
Okay.

23:34.333 --> 23:37.083
[gasping indistinctly]

23:41.834 --> 23:44.250
<i>♪ It's a new kind of beautiful ♪</i>

23:44.333 --> 23:45.500
Mommy.

23:47.709 --> 23:49.333
If you're ready to go,

23:49.417 --> 23:50.792
it's okay.

23:50.875 --> 23:53.041
We're gonna be okay.

23:53.125 --> 23:56.041
<i>♪ A new kind of beautiful, oh, oh ♪</i>

23:56.125 --> 23:58.875
[voice breaking] We love you.

23:58.959 --> 24:01.125
But we don't want you to suffer.

24:01.208 --> 24:02.250
<i>♪ Oh, oh ♪</i>

24:02.375 --> 24:07.291
I'm not r-ready.

24:07.875 --> 24:10.875
If you're tired, I understand.

24:10.959 --> 24:12.291
<i>♪ A new light ♪</i>

24:12.375 --> 24:13.375
I love you.

24:13.458 --> 24:14.333
<i>♪ Shining down on me ♪</i>

24:14.417 --> 24:16.333
Ready to die?

24:16.417 --> 24:17.500
<i>♪ A new way ♪</i>

24:17.583 --> 24:18.792
No.

24:18.875 --> 24:20.583
<i>♪ A new road ♪</i>

24:20.667 --> 24:24.291
I-I want to go home.

24:24.709 --> 24:27.625
<i>♪ Oh, oh ♪</i>

24:27.709 --> 24:30.208
<i>♪ To a new kind of beautiful ♪</i>

24:34.834 --> 24:36.959
[Ben] <i>Hey, you've reached Ben</i>
<i>Warren. Please leave a message.</i>

24:37.041 --> 24:39.959
-[beep]
-Yeah, I-- Ben? Um, it's my mom.

24:40.041 --> 24:43.333
I think she was just lucid with me,

24:43.417 --> 24:46.166
and she said some things
that I don't understand,

24:46.250 --> 24:48.417
and now I-I don't know what do,

24:48.500 --> 24:50.375
and I need someone to tell me what to do.

24:50.458 --> 24:53.667
Just, uh, call me as soon as you can.

24:54.291 --> 24:55.375
Uh, I love you.

24:55.583 --> 24:57.458
[siren wailing in distance]

24:59.959 --> 25:01.250
[Maggie] Hey.

25:01.333 --> 25:03.583
I saw you leave. I wanted to check.

25:04.542 --> 25:06.166
She said she's not ready to go.

25:07.291 --> 25:09.500
For a split second,

25:09.583 --> 25:12.250
my heart was filled up with so much joy.

25:13.208 --> 25:14.959
But now I'm just mad.

25:15.041 --> 25:18.625
Mad because no one told me she was sick,

25:19.542 --> 25:24.542
mad because she probably
has no idea what's happening.

25:25.917 --> 25:29.542
You know, if I'm being totally honest,

25:30.041 --> 25:32.709
I don't want her to suffer
from this Alzheimer's anymore.

25:32.792 --> 25:35.542
You know, it's a horrific disease,

25:35.625 --> 25:38.792
and I want her to be free.

25:38.875 --> 25:40.834
But I don't want COVID to be the reason.

25:40.917 --> 25:41.917
I d-- I don't want her

25:42.000 --> 25:45.291
to be just another Black woman statistic

25:45.375 --> 25:47.500
in this pandemic count.

25:47.583 --> 25:48.917
Yeah, I hear that.

25:49.750 --> 25:51.208
100%.

25:54.542 --> 25:55.959
None of this is easy.

25:56.125 --> 25:58.709
All of it is confusing and...

25:59.625 --> 26:02.083
[sighs] hard and awful.

26:02.166 --> 26:05.625
But even with Alzheimer's,
she's been healthy.

26:06.250 --> 26:09.208
And now I'm watching her struggle

26:09.291 --> 26:13.875
to do the most basic
of human reflexes-- breathing.

26:14.792 --> 26:17.125
And if she's saying
she's not ready to go...

26:19.458 --> 26:21.291
I don't know what to think.

26:22.291 --> 26:24.250
I felt so sure

26:24.333 --> 26:26.542
that she wouldn't want to live
like she's been living,

26:26.625 --> 26:29.792
but maybe I'm wrong, yeah?

26:29.875 --> 26:34.917
Maybe she's happy in the world
her mind takes her to.

26:35.000 --> 26:37.500
Now I'm questioning every choice I made.

26:37.583 --> 26:39.083
I mean, s-should I be doing more?

26:39.166 --> 26:42.542
Should I move her to the ICU?
Intubate her?

26:42.625 --> 26:44.792
Am I just thinking about how <i>I </i>feel

26:44.875 --> 26:48.083
instead of what's going on
with her-- inside of her mind?

26:49.917 --> 26:51.875
-Do you want my opinion?
-Please.

26:52.583 --> 26:56.166
I've been the one who does everything,

26:56.333 --> 27:00.792
who fights tooth and nail
against death at all costs.

27:02.250 --> 27:04.667
But truthfully, with my mom,

27:05.291 --> 27:07.417
it didn't give me
more peace of mind in the end.

27:09.291 --> 27:11.125
It might have done the opposite.

27:12.166 --> 27:17.250
I didn't think so at the time,
but it was the easier choice.

27:17.834 --> 27:20.166
To fall back on acting like a surgeon

27:20.250 --> 27:22.208
and searching for all the answers.

27:25.625 --> 27:29.542
Bailey, you've given your mom so much.

27:30.542 --> 27:32.625
She's gotten to raise you

27:32.709 --> 27:35.333
and watch you turn into
this incredible surgeon

27:35.417 --> 27:37.667
and chief of a hospital.

27:37.750 --> 27:39.417
She watched you fall in love.

27:39.792 --> 27:41.792
Twice. Twice!

27:42.417 --> 27:45.125
[laughs] And raise a family.

27:48.458 --> 27:52.875
Of course you're never going
to feel ready to say goodbye,

27:52.959 --> 27:54.083
but...

27:55.750 --> 27:57.709
she's had an amazing life.

27:58.333 --> 28:03.291
[Bailey] I brought my parents
to Seattle kicking and fighting.

28:03.375 --> 28:05.875
I promised them, if they moved here,

28:05.959 --> 28:08.041
it was the right thing to do

28:08.125 --> 28:10.792
so they could be closer
to their only daughter.

28:10.875 --> 28:14.291
I told them I knew best.
Just listen to me.

28:14.375 --> 28:17.291
And if they hadn't done that,
they would still be at home.

28:17.375 --> 28:18.709
Isolated.

28:18.792 --> 28:20.542
And Mom wouldn't be dying. Not yet.

28:20.625 --> 28:22.000
You don't know that.

28:22.083 --> 28:24.375
She was exposed at the place
that I set up for them.

28:25.000 --> 28:30.291
The-- The facility let someone
move in from New York,

28:30.625 --> 28:32.250
a retired surgeon.

28:32.875 --> 28:35.750
He became symptomatic
the day after his arrival.

28:36.125 --> 28:39.750
<i>After </i>they said they had
shut down to all outsiders,

28:39.834 --> 28:41.709
including family.

28:41.792 --> 28:43.458
How in the hell could you have
known that was going to happen?

28:43.542 --> 28:47.125
How could you have known
any of this was going to happen?

28:48.125 --> 28:50.625
Bailey, you cannot feel guilty about this.

28:50.709 --> 28:51.542
[chuckles]

28:56.208 --> 28:58.792
My mom, she left me five voicemails

28:58.875 --> 29:00.542
for my birthday last year.

29:00.625 --> 29:02.250
She kept calling

29:02.667 --> 29:04.333
because she forgot that she had already

29:04.417 --> 29:05.917
wished me happy birthday.

29:06.875 --> 29:08.000
There they are.

29:08.125 --> 29:10.667
[Elena] ♪ <i>Happy birthday to you </i>♪

29:10.750 --> 29:12.041
I never deleted them

29:12.125 --> 29:15.041
because I guess I realized

29:15.125 --> 29:18.041
that it might be the last time
she remembered at all.

29:18.125 --> 29:20.875
[phone clicks, singing stops]

29:20.959 --> 29:24.834
She raised me to be a good little girl.

29:24.917 --> 29:28.917
And even when I defied her...

29:29.000 --> 29:32.000
[chuckles] I was never disrespectful.

29:32.208 --> 29:35.750
And I tried to be good at everything.

29:36.375 --> 29:39.750
A good student, a good mother.

29:39.834 --> 29:42.792
Wife, doctor, chief.

29:43.375 --> 29:47.542
And now she just needs me
to be a good daughter,

29:47.625 --> 29:49.500
and I'm not sure how to do that,

29:49.583 --> 29:51.667
even though it's what I've been
the longest.

29:52.166 --> 29:53.959
You've chosen palliative care.

29:55.500 --> 29:58.417
You're giving her the best care possible

29:58.500 --> 30:01.250
while keeping her
as comfortable as possible.

30:02.125 --> 30:03.500
That is good.

30:03.709 --> 30:07.542
And it is kind and respectful

30:07.750 --> 30:08.917
and brave.

30:09.000 --> 30:11.709
<i>♪ I'm gonna lay down ♪</i>

30:11.792 --> 30:14.834
I wish I could've given my mom
a more dignified death.

30:14.917 --> 30:16.500
<i>♪ Lay down some roots,</i>
<i>This rolling stone ♪</i>

30:16.583 --> 30:21.250
But I pushed so hard.

30:21.333 --> 30:24.667
<i>♪ He's gonna lay down ♪</i>

30:25.500 --> 30:27.250
You know, it's her own damn fault, really.

30:27.917 --> 30:29.375
<i>♪ For you ♪</i>

30:29.458 --> 30:32.125
My whole life, she told me
to push through.

30:32.208 --> 30:34.166
[chuckles]

30:34.250 --> 30:36.291
Be strong. Fight the good fight.

30:37.208 --> 30:40.083
My mom was kind of the opposite.

30:40.166 --> 30:43.000
Like, overprotective, like, hovering.

30:43.083 --> 30:45.750
There was a reception

30:45.834 --> 30:48.750
sponsored by
the Daughters of the Revolution.

30:48.834 --> 30:50.750
They had given me a scholarship.

30:51.083 --> 30:52.500
[snorts]

30:52.583 --> 30:55.458
So my mom said
I should take the scholarship

30:55.542 --> 30:57.834
but not go to the reception.

30:57.917 --> 30:59.750
But I didn't want to give them
that satisfaction.

30:59.834 --> 31:02.291
No, I wanted them to see

31:02.375 --> 31:04.792
what "Miranda Bailey" looked like, right?

31:04.875 --> 31:08.875
So I went with my dad.

31:08.959 --> 31:10.834
[both laugh]

31:10.917 --> 31:13.917
We had a good laugh

31:14.000 --> 31:18.417
at those very proper ladies.

31:18.500 --> 31:20.250
I think you mean "white" ladies.

31:20.792 --> 31:22.875
-Uh... [laughs]
-Yeah.

31:22.959 --> 31:26.291
Watching them try to hide their horror

31:26.375 --> 31:29.875
when they saw who they had
given their scholarship to,

31:29.959 --> 31:32.375
-yeah, that was classic.
-[chuckles]

31:32.458 --> 31:34.208
Oh, and guidance counselors, oh, my God.

31:34.291 --> 31:36.709
Oh, yeah, yeah, always trying to suggest

31:36.792 --> 31:38.875
a school where we might
feel "more comfortable."

31:38.959 --> 31:41.709
"Oh, Wellesley.

31:41.792 --> 31:44.250
That's a fine school, Miranda.

31:44.333 --> 31:48.041
But, um, I think state school
is more your speed."

31:48.125 --> 31:49.917
-Mm-hmm.
-Like I don't know my speed.

31:50.000 --> 31:52.000
-Please.
-Try harder and do better

31:52.083 --> 31:53.625
just to be considered average.

31:53.709 --> 31:55.250
Or to be considered at all.

31:55.750 --> 31:59.125
But how they underestimate our greatness.

31:59.792 --> 32:02.333
-Graduated magna cum laude...
-Mm-hmm.

32:02.417 --> 32:05.834
...with my biology degree, by the way.

32:06.542 --> 32:11.250
And you better bet my mom cut
out the graduation announcement

32:11.333 --> 32:14.250
from Wellesley and mailed it
to my guidance counselor.

32:14.333 --> 32:17.166
[both laugh]

32:17.250 --> 32:19.250
[sighs deeply]

32:19.333 --> 32:22.166
[both chuckle]

32:22.250 --> 32:24.542
I don't know how I'm gonna do this.

32:26.458 --> 32:28.917
[sighs]

32:38.625 --> 32:41.542
Oh. Uh, I c-- I can come back.

32:41.625 --> 32:44.250
No. No, no, no. Uh, no,
I just finished up his EEG.

32:44.333 --> 32:46.083
I wanted to, um, make sure

32:46.166 --> 32:47.750
that the seizure was a one-and-done,

32:47.834 --> 32:51.375
before I head home,
take 10 scalding hot showers,

32:51.458 --> 32:53.250
and hug up on everybody.

32:53.333 --> 32:57.166
Um... Maggie says
that his numbers are holding.

32:57.250 --> 32:59.000
Good. Thanks.

33:00.667 --> 33:02.125
[door closes]

33:02.208 --> 33:03.750
[monitor beeping]

33:09.959 --> 33:11.625
I don't know if you were ignoring me

33:11.709 --> 33:13.125
when I came by the house

33:13.208 --> 33:15.041
or-- or if you were
just too sick to answer,

33:15.125 --> 33:17.291
but I-I'm-- I'm gonna go with too sick

33:17.375 --> 33:20.625
'cause then-- then maybe
there's a-a ray of hope for us,

33:20.709 --> 33:23.291
which I could really use right now,

33:23.375 --> 33:24.792
and I know you could.

33:26.750 --> 33:27.917
You know, I'm-- I'm gonna stop asking.

33:28.000 --> 33:29.208
I'm just gonna decide.

33:29.291 --> 33:33.375
I-I'm deciding that
we mean enough to each other

33:33.458 --> 33:35.917
that, even though I hurt you and I-I...

33:37.333 --> 33:39.500
I hurt you more than I could ever imagine,

33:39.583 --> 33:41.542
that a repair could be made, that...

33:45.041 --> 33:48.041
maybe you could... remember

33:48.125 --> 33:49.834
some of the things
that you don't hate about me

33:49.917 --> 33:52.041
and we-- we could salvage
our friendship because...

33:54.875 --> 33:56.750
I don't know how we're going
to get through this pandemic,

33:56.834 --> 33:58.667
but I do know-- I do know

33:58.750 --> 34:00.500
that we're not going
to get through it alone.

34:00.583 --> 34:03.417
So if you want
to have nothing to do with me,

34:03.500 --> 34:04.959
then you are just going
to have to get all better

34:05.041 --> 34:06.333
and tell me yourself,

34:06.417 --> 34:08.166
because until I hear you say the words,

34:08.250 --> 34:09.667
you're not gonna get rid of me.

34:14.500 --> 34:16.041
Oh, my God. Tom. Tom?

34:16.583 --> 34:17.875
Tom, can you hear me?

34:18.875 --> 34:20.667
It's me. It's-- It's Teddy.

34:21.458 --> 34:22.709
[Koracick] You were wrong.

34:23.208 --> 34:24.709
Wrong about what?

34:24.792 --> 34:26.166
<i>♪ The setting free ♪</i>

34:26.250 --> 34:28.291
When you came to my house.

34:28.375 --> 34:29.792
I was ignoring you.

34:29.875 --> 34:32.333
<i>♪ The bittersweet but sweet release ♪</i>

34:32.417 --> 34:36.709
Did you hear everything I-I just said?

34:36.792 --> 34:38.834
<i>♪ A heavy sky ♪</i>

34:38.917 --> 34:40.959
[chuckles] I hate you.

34:41.041 --> 34:42.458
<i>♪ Hangs on the sea ♪</i>

34:42.542 --> 34:44.291
Well, we both know that's not true.

34:46.333 --> 34:48.166
[laughs, wheezes]

34:48.542 --> 34:50.166
[sighs] Hey.

34:52.542 --> 34:54.542
What would you say to a sponge bath?

34:54.917 --> 34:56.250
[laughs]

34:56.333 --> 34:58.041
Well, but, you know, as friends.

34:58.625 --> 35:00.709
Friendly sponge bath. [chuckles]

35:00.792 --> 35:06.083
<i>♪ I am lifted, I am lifted ♪</i>

35:06.166 --> 35:10.959
<i>♪ I am lifted, I am free ♪</i>

35:11.041 --> 35:16.625
<i>♪ I've been holding on,</i>
<i>I've been holding on ♪</i>

35:16.709 --> 35:21.834
<i>♪ I've been holding on, now I'm lifted ♪</i>

35:23.583 --> 35:26.125
<i>♪ We can learn to love ♪</i>

35:29.000 --> 35:30.375
Hey.

35:30.458 --> 35:31.959
I rounded on all of Bailey's patients.

35:32.041 --> 35:35.000
DeLuca said he'll keep an eye on
them for the rest of the night.

35:35.083 --> 35:36.291
Yeah, thank you.

35:36.667 --> 35:38.750
Yeah, I hesitate to ask,
but how's her mom doing?

35:39.208 --> 35:41.291
They don't expect her to last the night.

35:41.625 --> 35:45.125
<i>♪ Everything is beautiful ♪</i>

35:45.208 --> 35:46.333
That's-- [sighs]

35:46.417 --> 35:48.250
<i>♪ I am lifted, I am lifted ♪</i>

35:48.333 --> 35:50.667
You realize half of our COVID
patients are Black and brown?

35:50.750 --> 35:51.792
I know.

35:51.875 --> 35:53.834
In a city that's 7% Black?

35:53.917 --> 35:56.250
Like, how does that even compute?

35:56.333 --> 35:58.041
It doesn't.

35:58.125 --> 36:00.709
If I hear one more person blame
it on pre-existing conditions

36:00.792 --> 36:03.250
as if the conditions aren't
manmade to begin with...

36:03.750 --> 36:06.875
Like we're not pushed into
the front line of all of our jobs

36:06.959 --> 36:09.000
and forced to live
in overcrowded situations,

36:09.083 --> 36:11.250
surrounded by environmental hazards.

36:11.333 --> 36:12.875
Yeah, people want to make

36:12.959 --> 36:15.041
everything bad
that happens your own fault.

36:15.125 --> 36:16.750
Yeah, when systemic racism is the root

36:16.834 --> 36:18.750
of the whole damn thing. Forget the pre-,

36:18.834 --> 36:20.458
it's the existing condition.

36:20.542 --> 36:21.959
Existing while Black.

36:22.834 --> 36:26.542
<i>♪ I am lifted, I am free ♪</i>

36:26.625 --> 36:28.208
<i>♪ I've been holding on ♪</i>

36:28.291 --> 36:30.291
You know, Richard, we both know
my mom is stubborn.

36:30.750 --> 36:32.208
<i>♪ I've been holding on too long ♪</i>

36:32.291 --> 36:34.000
And everything she's been
through, I feel like

36:34.083 --> 36:36.208
she thinks she's invincible now,
and she's not.

36:37.083 --> 36:38.166
<i>♪ I've been holding on too long ♪</i>

36:38.250 --> 36:39.792
We can't lose her, Richard.

36:41.375 --> 36:43.375
The world can't lose her, you know?

36:43.458 --> 36:44.917
It's been handled.

36:46.041 --> 36:47.291
Oh, you talked to her?

36:47.583 --> 36:49.125
Oh, good.

36:49.208 --> 36:50.125
What'd you say?

36:50.250 --> 36:53.208
I think it's best kept between us.

36:53.750 --> 36:55.458
Why are you being weird about it?

36:56.583 --> 36:58.041
'Cause it's about sex, isn't it?

36:58.792 --> 37:01.250
-It is.
-Thanks. Right. Good night.

37:01.333 --> 37:02.917
[clears throat]

37:06.959 --> 37:10.083
Oh, my God. That smells so good.

37:10.166 --> 37:11.667
We're sharing, right?

37:11.750 --> 37:14.250
Pod together, eat together?
Please say yes.

37:14.333 --> 37:15.834
I delivered a baby today.

37:16.875 --> 37:17.917
-Is that a yes?
-Yes!

37:18.000 --> 37:19.291
-Oh.
-Yes, yes.

37:19.375 --> 37:21.041
Wait, weren't we together all day?

37:21.125 --> 37:23.625
What do you mean
you delivered a secret baby?

37:23.709 --> 37:26.083
Happened very quick.
I went to check on Luna,

37:26.166 --> 37:28.375
and this nurse said that there
was an imminent delivery,

37:28.458 --> 37:32.291
and the next second,
I was catching a baby.

37:33.375 --> 37:37.875
I was literally the first person
in the universe to hold him.

37:37.959 --> 37:39.792
And then I handed him to his parents,

37:39.875 --> 37:41.875
and their faces were just...

37:43.166 --> 37:45.083
No wonder Val's so depressed.

37:45.208 --> 37:47.583
It's the happiest thing I've ever seen.

37:47.667 --> 37:52.500
It was just so pure and simple
and perfect.

37:52.583 --> 37:54.000
I was buzzing.

37:54.083 --> 37:55.792
But it was a total random fluke,

37:55.917 --> 37:58.667
and tomorrow, I'll be back
to the same depressing crap.

37:58.750 --> 38:01.333
I mean, you did save Val's life today.

38:02.583 --> 38:04.166
You think that's why Carina DeLuca

38:04.250 --> 38:05.959
-is always in such a good mood?
-[chuckles]

38:06.041 --> 38:07.667
She's just, you know, handing out babies,

38:07.750 --> 38:09.917
and it shoots her serotonin
level through the roof.

38:10.000 --> 38:14.208
Well, yeah, but doesn't she also
have, like, an orgasm hobby?

38:15.083 --> 38:16.625
What if I changed?

38:16.709 --> 38:18.291
Changed what?

38:18.375 --> 38:19.917
Careers. Programs.

38:20.000 --> 38:21.834
-[Chuckles]
-Is that insane?

38:22.250 --> 38:24.500
-[sighs]
-Khan did it, and what he did

38:24.583 --> 38:27.291
is so much harder
than switching specialties.

38:27.375 --> 38:29.625
He started over with nothing.

38:29.709 --> 38:32.166
And I know-- I know
I've put years into surgery,

38:32.250 --> 38:34.250
but if it's not bringing me any joy,

38:35.375 --> 38:38.917
then wouldn't it be insane to <i>not </i>change?

38:39.750 --> 38:43.834
I think you eat and then sleep
before you make any major li--

38:43.917 --> 38:45.709
Oh, my God. I sound like my mother.

38:46.667 --> 38:48.375
-[sighs]
-I want to be happy.

38:49.625 --> 38:52.166
Everyone's dying. Meredith's--

38:54.000 --> 38:56.792
Tomorrow is not promised.

38:56.875 --> 38:58.458
Not in marriage.

38:58.542 --> 38:59.750
Not in life.

39:00.375 --> 39:01.750
I want to be happy.

39:08.208 --> 39:09.792
She's decompensating.

39:11.625 --> 39:12.834
You should go in.

39:15.375 --> 39:17.333
She barely knows who I am.

39:18.458 --> 39:21.166
And I want to be there for her.

39:21.250 --> 39:24.500
I-I want her husband to be there for her.

39:24.583 --> 39:29.041
She deserves to be surrounded
by love and family.

39:30.750 --> 39:32.792
But Dad's in quarantine.

39:32.875 --> 39:36.709
He's high-risk, and I don't
want him to expose anyone.

39:36.792 --> 39:38.709
I don't want him to be exposed.

39:38.792 --> 39:42.166
I know this is not what
you imagined for your mother.

39:42.250 --> 39:44.166
And I'm sorry about that.

39:45.750 --> 39:47.333
But she needs you now.

39:49.542 --> 39:50.667
It's time.

39:52.208 --> 39:53.583
And if you don't go in,

39:53.667 --> 39:55.834
I promise you will never forgive yourself.

39:59.000 --> 40:00.792
[crying] I'm scared.

40:01.750 --> 40:03.125
<i>♪ I've got sunshine ♪</i>

40:03.208 --> 40:04.500
I know.

40:06.125 --> 40:08.000
We'll do it together.

40:08.083 --> 40:09.750
[Bailey] <i>Patients lose their power</i>

40:09.834 --> 40:12.667
<i>when they are referred to</i>
<i>as "Bed number 4"</i>

40:12.750 --> 40:15.333
<i>or "arm pain guy." </i>[sighs]

40:15.417 --> 40:16.625
<i>♪ I've got the month of May ♪</i>

40:16.709 --> 40:18.959
<i>Even in their deaths,</i>

40:19.041 --> 40:21.500
<i>they are not faceless.</i>

40:21.583 --> 40:23.709
<i>They are not nameless.</i>

40:24.667 --> 40:27.041
<i>They are more than statistics.</i>

40:27.125 --> 40:30.208
<i>♪ What can make me feel this way? ♪</i>

40:30.291 --> 40:32.166
[door closes]

40:32.250 --> 40:34.166
<i>More than </i><i>"co-morbid conditions"</i>

40:34.250 --> 40:36.166
<i>or "nursing-home patients."</i>

40:36.250 --> 40:38.125
<i>♪ My girl ♪</i>

40:38.208 --> 40:41.709
<i>They are sons, brothers, </i><i>and uncles</i>

40:41.792 --> 40:43.291
<i>who speak five languages</i>

40:43.375 --> 40:47.542
<i>and run restaurants-- </i><i>Wade Klein, 66.</i>

40:47.625 --> 40:49.125
<i>♪ My girl ♪</i>

40:49.208 --> 40:52.375
<i>They are great-grandfathers</i>
<i>who love Broadway--</i>

40:52.458 --> 40:55.333
<i>Jacob Lappin, 92.</i>

40:55.417 --> 40:58.583
<i>♪ I don't need no money ♪</i>

40:59.834 --> 41:03.875
<i>♪ Fortune or fame ♪</i>

41:04.667 --> 41:07.417
<i>♪ I got all the riches, baby ♪</i>

41:07.500 --> 41:11.417
<i>They are baseball-loving nurses</i>
<i>with an easy laugh--</i>

41:11.500 --> 41:14.000
<i>Dane Wilson, 45.</i>

41:14.083 --> 41:18.917
<i>♪ I guess you'd say ♪</i>

41:20.000 --> 41:23.750
<i>♪ What can make me feel ♪</i>

41:23.834 --> 41:25.625
<i>-♪ This way? ♪</i>
<i>-♪ This way? ♪</i>

41:26.625 --> 41:28.834
<i>-♪ My girl ♪</i>
<i>-♪ My girl ♪</i>

41:30.125 --> 41:34.333
<i>♪ Talking 'bout my girl ♪</i>

41:37.709 --> 41:39.250
<i>♪ My girl ♪</i>

41:39.333 --> 41:40.500
It's okay.

41:42.333 --> 41:43.458
<i>♪ My girl ♪</i>

41:43.625 --> 41:44.625
Okay.

41:45.125 --> 41:48.583
<i>They are the world's </i><i>greatest mothers,</i>

41:48.667 --> 41:51.750
<i>and they are </i><i>the most beloved wives --</i>

41:52.041 --> 41:55.709
<i>Elena Rose Bailey, 84.</i>
